commit_list.repo_description: Target recognition based on biological visual information processing mechanism is one of the hot topics in the field of computer vision, based on convolutional neural network, this paper simulates the mechanism of human brain layer information processing. Firstly, the model is based on the direction selectivity, spatial locality, and the lateral inhibition between neurons in the retina; Secondly, the algorithm introduces the sparse expression characteristics of biological neural cells to construct a new neural synaptic activation function, and follow the process of random variation of the local current in the nerve fiber film to overcome the common problem of over fitting in the neural network calculation; On the basis of this, a hierarchical visual perception algorithm is proposed, which is based on the computation of perceptual invariance and the ability of learning and recognition, so as to realize the calculation model of the visual path information characteristic, which is abstract, complex and integrated. Finally, the simulation experiment, application different scale data set test the proposed algorithm, results show that the proposed algorithm for target identification problem of large-scale, with good recognition effect, the average accurate rate of more than 85% of the target recognition.
